  "text": "This simple, yet powerful approach can be easily applied to a range of joint prediction tasks. In prior work, joint models have been designed for a specific language. For instance, joint models for Chinese are designed with word segmentation in mind [CITATION_1] , while algorithms for processing Semitic languages are tailored for morpho-logical analysis [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In contrast, we show that our algorithm can be effortlessly applied to all these distinct languages. Language-specific characteristics drive the lattice construction and the feature selection, while the learning and inference methods are languageagnostic.",
